        "rendered": "Site Logo block"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go to the List of Blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Site Logo</em> block lets you add a logo or image representing your website identity and help increase brand recognition. Unlike a site icon or a favicon, a logo is only visible on website pages like the home page.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-info\" style=\"background: #e5f5fa;border-left: 5px solid #00a0d2;padding: 1.5em 3em 1.6em 3.7em;margin-bottom: 1.5em\"><p><em><strong>Note:</strong> </em>The Site Logo block is primarily used when editing the Template files in the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/site-editor/\">Site Editor</a>.</p></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to use the Site Logo block</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a <em>Site Logo</em> block, create a new page or open the Site Editor. Click the Block Inserter icon and search for the <em>Site Logo</em> Block. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also type <kbd>/site-logo</kbd> and hit enter in a new paragraph block to add the <em>Site Logo</em> block quickly.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"722\" height=\"374\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-29-at-9.13.03-AM.png\" alt=\"How to add Site Logo block by typing the block name\" class=\"wp-image-15782315\" style=\"width:361px;height:187px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-29-at-9.13.03-AM.png 722w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-29-at-9.13.03-AM-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 722px) 100vw, 722px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">How to add Site Logo block quickly</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the <em>Site Logo</em> placeholder icon and upload a new image or select one from the Media Library. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have added an image logo, you can resize it using the drag handles.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1563\" height=\"845\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/site-logo.gif\" alt=\"A demonstration on how to add and customize site logo block\" class=\"wp-image-16356604\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you add an image to the <em>Site Logo </em>block, the change applies to all <em>Site Logo</em> blocks on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To use the site logo image as the site icon in browser tabs, bookmark bars, and WordPress mobile apps, access the <em>Site Logo</em> block settings panel and enable the Use as site icon option. It automatically set the image in the <em>Site Logo </em>block as the site icon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"347\" height=\"412\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/image.png\" alt=\"The use as site icon option for the site logo block\" class=\"wp-image-16356617\" style=\"width:298px;height:354px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/image.png 347w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/image-253x300.png 253w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A block toolbar lets you customize or modify each block in the editor. Select the <em>Site Logo</em> block to view its block toolbar. Below is a list of tools shown in this block toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Block-moving tools</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change alignment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Apply duotone filter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Crop </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replace</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Transform to</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/transform.png\" alt=\"The transform to button\" class=\"wp-image-16356605\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/transform.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/transform-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Transform to</strong> button lets you convert the <em>Site Logo</em> block into a <em>Columns</em>, <em>Group</em>, or <em>Site Title</em> block. You can also change the <em>Site Logo</em> block style from <strong>Default </strong>to <strong>Rounded</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block-moving tools</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/moving.png\" alt=\"The block-moving tools\" class=\"wp-image-16356606\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/moving.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/moving-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the block-moving tools to move the <em>Site Logo</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The drag or six dots icon allows you to freely reposition the block anywhere within the editor by holding the icon and dragging it to the new location.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, you can also use the arrows icon to move the block left or right within the group of nested blocks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/site-logo-block/\">Get more information about moving a block within the editor.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Change alignment</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/align.png\" alt=\"The change alignment button\" class=\"wp-image-16356607\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/align.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/align-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <strong>Change alignment</strong> tool to modify the alignment of the <em>Site Logo</em> block. Select the icon and pick one of the following alignment options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>None \u2013 is the default block size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align left \u2013 makes the block left-aligned.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align center \u2013 lets you align the block to the center.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align right \u2013 makes the block right-aligned.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Apply duotone filter</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/duotone.png\" alt=\"The apply duotone filter option\" class=\"wp-image-16356608\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/duotone.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/duotone-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Apply duotone filter</strong> option lets you create a two-tone color effect on the site logo without changing the original image. Note that the duotone effect works best on high-contrast images.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To apply the duotone filter, click the icon and choose the two colors from the provided duotone presets. You can create custom duotone colors using the Shadows and Highlights options. Choose from the provided color presets on each option, or use the color picker to set the custom colors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to undo all the changes, use the Clear button.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Crop</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/crop.png\" alt=\"The crop button\" class=\"wp-image-16356609\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/crop.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/crop-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <strong>Crop</strong> icon to adjust the site logo image. When clicked, it will display a set of tools for cropping the image. Below is a list of the Crop tools:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Zoom \u2013 enlarges the image by up to 300%.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Aspect Ratio \u2013 modifies the image\u2019s aspect ratio with the choices in the dropdown list.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rotate \u2013 revolves around the site logo image.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Apply \u2013 confirms or keeps the site logo image customization.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cancel \u2013 discards any changes to the site logo image.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The Crop button only appears in the block toolbar after you have inserted an image into the <em>Site Logo</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Replace</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/replace.png\" alt=\"The replace button\" class=\"wp-image-16356610\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/replace.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/replace-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Replace </strong>option lets you change the site logo by choosing another image from the Media Library or uploading a new one from your local computer. You can also remove the site logo image by clicking Reset.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"704\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/options.png\" alt=\"The more option button\" class=\"wp-image-16356611\" style=\"width:528px;height:75px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/options.png 704w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/options-300x43.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Option</strong> icon on the <em>Site Logo</em> block toolbar lets you access more block options. A drop-down menu will appear when you click it, and below is a list of actions you can do with the <em>Site Logo </em>block:.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read detailed information about the Other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress blocks have specific configuration options in the block settings panel. To access the <em>Site Logo</em> block settings panel, click the Settings button at the top-right corner of the editor. Moreover, the <em>Site Logo</em> block settings panel is divided into two tabs \u2013 <strong>Settings </strong>and <strong>Styles</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Settings </strong>tab has several options as follows:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Media</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"530\" height=\"203\" data-id=\"16359626\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/02/image.png\" alt=\"Add site logo to media gallery - block settings view before media is added\" class=\"wp-image-16359626\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/02/image.png 530w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/02/image-300x115.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The &#8220;add media&#8221; button to insert a site logo</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"565\" height=\"449\" data-id=\"16359627\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/02/image-1.png\" alt=\"Add or replace site logo in the media gallery - block settings view\" class=\"wp-image-16359627\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/02/image-1.png 565w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2024/02/image-1-300x238.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 565px) 100vw, 565px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Options to replace the site logo</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The media settings allows you to add an image to the <em>Site Logo</em> block. Here are the steps you can do with this settings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click Add media to add an image to the&nbsp;<em>Site Logo</em>&nbsp;block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Once an image has been added, click the image name to update the image.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You have three options to do so: select an image from the media library, upload a new image, or remove the image by resetting the media.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"419\" height=\"540\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings.png\" alt=\"The block settings options\" class=\"wp-image-16356612\" style=\"width:314px;height:405px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings.png 419w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/settings-233x300.png 233w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 419px) 100vw, 419px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Change the image width using the slider or typing a numeric value in the text field next to the slider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Enable the <strong>Link image to home</strong> option to make a hyperlink to your website\u2019s home page. This option is turned on by default.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Turn on the <strong>Open in new tab</strong> option to automatically open the home page in a new tab when the site logo image is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Activate the <strong>Use as site icon</strong> option to set the site logo image as the site icon. A site icon is a small image next to the site title in a web browser tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note that this option is only available after you add an image to the <em>Site Logo</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Advanced</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"414\" height=\"233\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/css.png\" alt=\"The advanced custom CSS option\" class=\"wp-image-16356613\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/css.png 414w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/css-300x169.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 414px) 100vw, 414px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Advanced section lets you add CSS class(es) to the <em>Site Logo</em> block. This will allow you to write custom CSS and styles for the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"404\" height=\"218\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/image-1.png\" alt=\"The apply globally for site logo styles\" class=\"wp-image-16356618\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/image-1.png 404w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/image-1-300x162.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 404px) 100vw, 404px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also apply the block styles to all <em>Site Logo</em> blocks by clicking the <strong>Apply globally</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Styles</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Styles tab has the following options:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Styles</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"413\" height=\"153\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/styles.png\" alt=\"The styles options\" class=\"wp-image-16356615\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/styles.png 413w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/styles-300x111.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 413px) 100vw, 413px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the Styles option to change the look of the <em>Site Logo</em> block. The initial configuration for the block\u2019s style is Default. You can change the site logo shape to round by clicking the <strong>Rounded </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dimensions</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"415\" height=\"389\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/dimensions.png\" alt=\"The dimensions option\" class=\"wp-image-16356616\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/dimensions.png 415w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/dimensions-300x281.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 415px) 100vw, 415px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dimensions option adds additional settings for the <em>Site Logo</em> block, where you can set custom width, padding, and margin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Learn more about the Dimensions settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2024-02-20\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated to content for WordPress 6.3</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2023-04-05\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated to content for WordPress 6.2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2022-06-29</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
